KW  - High-frequency trading
KW  - Intraday
KW  - International markets
KW  - Momentum
KW  - Market characteristics
AB  - We examine intraday time series momentum (ITSM) in an international setting by employing high-frequency data of 16 developed markets. We show that ITSM is economically sizable and statistically significant both in- and out-of-sample in most countries. Based on theories of investor behavior, we propose and test four hypotheses to reveal the source of ITSM profitability. We document both in the cross-section and time series dimension that ITSM is stronger when liquidity is low, volatility is high, and new information is discrete. Overall, our results suggest that the ITSM is driven by both market microstructure and behavioral factors.
